Use the standard library
This is how to unique of l:
   Remember that sorted is bubble_sort of l
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that n is sorted's length
   When n is 0, then:
      The answer is result
   End when
   Remember that last is item 0 in sorted
   Add result to last
   Remember that i is 1
   Do this diff of n and 1 times:
      Remember that x is item i in sorted
      When x is not last, then:
         Add result to x
         Remember that last is x
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> unique of [5, 3, 5, 2, 3, 3, 9, 0, 123] 
[0, 2, 3, 5, 9, 123]
>>> unique of [] 
[]
>>> unique of [7] 
[7]
>>> unique of [4, 4, 4, 4] 
[4]
>>> unique of [3, 1, 2, 1, 3] 
[1, 2, 3]